<subSubSection pageId="15" pageNumber="16" type="discussion">
<paragraph blockId="15.[264,1323,284,430]" pageId="15" pageNumber="16">
<emphasis box="[312,414,284,309]" italics="true" pageId="15" pageNumber="16">Remarks</emphasis>
: Externally this species resembles 
<taxonomicName box="[836,885,284,309]" class="Insecta" family="Cicadellidae" genus="Scaphoideus" kingdom="Animalia" order="Hemiptera" pageId="15" pageNumber="16" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="kirti">
<emphasis box="[836,885,284,309]" italics="true" pageId="15" pageNumber="16">kirti</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
and 
<taxonomicName authority="Kitbamroong &amp; Freytag" authorityName="Kitbamroong &amp; Freytag" box="[946,1323,284,310]" class="Insecta" family="Cicadellidae" genus="Scaphoideus" kingdom="Animalia" order="Hemiptera" pageId="15" pageNumber="16" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="knappi">
<emphasis box="[946,1026,284,309]" italics="true" pageId="15" pageNumber="16">knappi</emphasis>
Kitbamroong &amp; Freytag
</taxonomicName>
in coloration and structure. However, the vertex is more elongate and more acutely pointed in 
<emphasis box="[293,381,364,389]" italics="true" pageId="15" pageNumber="16">
<taxonomicName box="[293,376,364,389]" class="Insecta" family="Cicadellidae" genus="Scaphoideus" kingdom="Animalia" order="Hemiptera" pageId="15" pageNumber="16" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="bifidus">bifidus</taxonomicName>
,
</emphasis>
and the aedeagus has a pair of median anteriorly directed processes that 
<taxonomicName box="[1225,1274,364,389]" class="Insecta" family="Cicadellidae" genus="Scaphoideus" kingdom="Animalia" order="Hemiptera" pageId="15" pageNumber="16" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="kirti">
<emphasis box="[1225,1274,364,389]" italics="true" pageId="15" pageNumber="16">kirti</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
and 
<taxonomicName box="[264,344,404,429]" class="Insecta" family="Cicadellidae" genus="Scaphoideus" kingdom="Animalia" order="Hemiptera" pageId="15" pageNumber="16" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="knappi">
<emphasis box="[264,344,404,429]" italics="true" pageId="15" pageNumber="16">knappi</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
both lack.
</paragraph>
